QuestionEN:
As shown in the figure, in the plane rectangular coordinate system, quadrilateral OABC is a square with side length 8, D is the midpoint of OA, point E lies on AB such that AE = $\frac{3}{4}$AB, P(x, m) is a moving point on segments CD and DE, and Q(x, n) is a moving point on segment CE. The points P and Q are connected by PQ.  

(1) Find the areas of triangle ADE and triangle OCD;  
(2) Express the quantitative relationship between m and x using an equation;  
(3) Directly write the coordinates of point Q when the length of segment PQ equals 3.

AnswerEN:
(1) $S_{\triangle ADE}=12$, $S_{\triangle OCD}=16$;  
(2) $m=-2x+8$ $(0\leqslant x\leqslant 4)$ or $m=\dfrac{3}{2}x-6$ $(4\leqslant x\leqslant 8)$;  
(3) The coordinates of point Q are $\left(\dfrac{12}{7}, \dfrac{53}{7}\right)$ or $\left(\dfrac{44}{7}, \dfrac{45}{7}\right)$.

