QuestionEN:
As shown in Figure 1, the parabola \( C_1: y = ax^2 + bx - 3 \) intersects the x-axis at points \( A(-1, 0) \) and \( B(3, 0) \), and intersects the y-axis at point \( C \).  
(1) Find the equation of the parabola;  
(2) Point \( P \) lies on the parabola. If the incenter of \( \triangle ACP \) happens to lie on the y-axis, determine the coordinates of point \( P \);  
(3) As shown in Figure 2, the parabola \( C_1 \) is shifted right by one unit to obtain parabola \( C_2 \). Points \( M \) and \( N \) both lie on \( C_2 \), in the fourth and second quadrants respectively. The line \( MN \) intersects the x-axis and y-axis at points \( E \) and \( F \). Given \( \angle NOF = \angle MOE \), prove that the line \( MN \) passes through a fixed point.  
[Note] This problem includes both proof and solution parts. Only the solution parts are to be answered.

AnswerCN:
(1)抛物线的解析式为y=x^2−2x−3;
(2)点P的坐标为(5,12);
(3)直线MN经过定点(4,−1).

AnswerEN:
(1) The equation of the parabola is \( y = x^2 - 2x - 3 \);  
(2) The coordinates of point P are \( (5, 12) \);  
(3) The straight line MN passes through the fixed point \( (4, -1) \).

