QuestionEN:
It is known that Xiaotian's home, the stationery store, and the park are located in order on the same straight line. The stationery store is 0.6 km away from Xiaotian's home, and the park is 0.8 km away from Xiaotian's home. Starting from home, Xiaotian first walked at a constant speed for 8 minutes to the stationery store; after leaving the stationery store, he walked at a constant speed for another 3 minutes to the park for exercise; after leaving the park, he walked at a constant speed for 10 minutes to return home. In the graph below, \( x \) represents time, and \( y \) represents the distance from home. The graph reflects the correspondence between Xiaotian's distance from home and time during this process.

\[
\begin{array}{c}
\text{↑} \quad y \text{ (km)} \\
\begin{tikzpicture}
\draw (0,0) -- (6,0) node[right]{$x$ (min)};
